Package klykov.graph

Class GraphMap<T>

java.lang.Object
klykov.graph.GraphMap<T>
Type Parameters:
T - There is a parameter for creating a graph of any type of objects or primitives.
All Implemented Interfaces:
Graph<T>
public class GraphMap<T> extends Object implements Graph<T>
The class implements the interface Graph and creates the data structure based on HashMap. It is possible to create a graph on your own or use the class Handler.
See Also:
Handler

    • graph

      private Map<T,​Set<T>> graph
      The graph is a map stores vertices and their adjacent vertices. The Set as the key of the map has been chosen because we need operations "add", "contains" and auto checking of uniqueness.
